                      /
                      <span>16</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-11-29</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>As Dean and Professor at the Alan Shawn Feinstein Graduate School at Johnson & Wales University I have adopted Mr. krames book as the major theme for our 700 MBA students.  The succint, valid, and sophisticated manner in which Mr. Krames transmits Mr. Welch's ideas and philosphies is remarkable.  The next best thing to Jack Welch is Jeffrey Krames and this book is the inner psyche of one of the world's greatest business legends.  I strongly recommend this book to instructors, business leaders, and managers in every field.  It is a one stop shopping trip of the wisdom and intellectual stimulation provided by Jack Welch through his alter ego, Jeffrey Krames.  This book should be on the list of every "Great Business Books" series for the world's top business schools and on the shelf of every manager anywhere in the world.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A Jack Welch Primer/Thesaurus</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>0</span>
