                      <span>2</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2001-11-24</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This is a great find for the reader who wants to truly understand what makes Jack Welch such an icon.  For years, I've been subjected to "Welchisms", loosely tossed about by everyone from managemenet consultants to managerial wannabes.   <br>In "The Jack Welch Lexicon of Leadership", the author provides a comprehensive look beyond the man to his underlying principles.  He discusses the significance of each and highlights Welch's initiatives within the perspective of the man's career as a trailblazer.  Best of all, it's succinct, which is more than I can say about some of the amateur "Welchism" purveyors I've encountered over the years!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Practical and Inspiring</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
